
1. EXECUTIVE SUMMARY

CVSS v3 9.8
ATTENTION: Exploitable remotely/low attack complexity
Vendor: Siemens
Equipment: Web Server of SCALANCE X200
Vulnerabilities: Heap-based Buffer Overflow, Stack-based Buffer Overflow

2. UPDATE INFORMATION
This updated advisory is a follow-up to the original advisory titled ICSA-21-103-07 Siemens Web Server of SCALANCE X200 that was published April 13, 2021, on the ICS webpage on us-cert.cisa.gov.
3. RISK EVALUATION
Successful exploitation of these vulnerabilities could cause a buffer overflow condition resulting in remote code execution.
